title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, no data is returned. The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: No data is returned in the query result page when calling a stored procedure from Oracle database.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Call a stored procedure from Oracle database.
2. Check the query result page to see that no data is returned.

Expected behavior:
- The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
